rComments: All exams were open-book take-home format and answers could easily be found in your notes, make sure you take good notes because some info was only said aloud. I managed without doing any of the readings (materials were shared online by the prof) and only looked quickly through them for anything I was missing in my notes. Only 1 midterm and 1 final
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments:
The class content was easy to understand and the lectures were rather straightfoward. BEWARE of her tests!! The TAs graded very harshly and the professor stood by how our work needs to be of "quality". Most of the test answers can be found in the powerpoints or lecture recordings.

Lectures were recorded but were also deleted a few days later.

Her class was my fav of the semester. The lectures are entertaining and I feel like I learned a lot . We only had 1 midterm, 1 project and 1 final. She's nice, answers emails, slides are on Brightspace and lectures are recorded. Her tests are ultra specific, you need to have watched lectures. People were surprised, so take notes + remember details

Prof Lopes is super sweet , and tried her best to make bimodal class interesting with participation and guest speakers, but her lectures were disorganized at times, and exam questions were very specific and not clear, but take homes with time to ask questions. Gave a small assignment as easy extra credit. Never talked about readings in class.

She is so sweet! The class is fairly interesting although the online format makes it hard to stay engaged. Very interesting and not a harsh grader. She brought in guest lecturers and really tried her best to make us participate although Zoom classrooms are hardly the most animated.

At the start of the semester, the prof seemed really sweet! Her exams are open-book and there's no time limit on them. But, the TA's graded SO harshly. They acted like we were all 4th year anthropology majors, when most of us were taking it as an elective. There's only 3 things considered for the grade, and she seemed a little unprepared sometimes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']
